column12: Filter circuit and connector using the same
column13: A filter circuit includes at least one signal channel between a cable side and a PCB side. The signal channel includes a parallel transformer connecting with the cable side and a two-wire CMC connecting the parallel transformer and the PCB side. The parallel transformer has a first magnetic wire and a second magnetic wire. The first magnetic wire has two first ends connected to the first side. The second magnetic wire has two second ends connected to the two-wire CMC and a center tap between the two second ends. Besides the filter circuit has at least one core coil. The center tap is electrically connected to the PCB side through the core coil.

column12: Display panel and dielectric apparatus with ESD protection effect
column13: A display panel and an electric apparatus with ESD protection effect are disclosed. The display panel comprises a panel substrate and patterned conductive layers stacked over the panel substrate. The display panel also has an array display area and a driving area. A first conductive layer of the patterned conductive layers comprises substantially repetitive patterns inside the driving area. The first conductive layer also has a dummy bar formed beside an edge pattern of the substantially repetitive patterns.
column15: CHEN SHIH-HAN;;TSAI SHAN-HUNG

column12: Display panel and electric apparatus with ESD protection effect
column13: A display panel and an electric apparatus with ESD protection effect are disclosed. The display panel comprises a panel substrate and patterned conductive layers stacked over the panel substrate. The display panel also has an array display area and a driving area. A first conductive layer of the patterned conductive layers comprises substantially-repetitive patterns inside the driving area. The first conductive layer also has a dummy bar formed beside an edge pattern of the substantially-repetitive patterns. The dummy bar, when the display panel is properly powered, electrically floats in the display panel and is isolated from any power sources, such that the dummy bar is capable of protecting the edge pattern from ESD damage.

column12: IMAGE CAPTURING METHOD AND MONITORING APPARATUS WITH SUPPLEMENTAL LIGHTING MODULATION
column13: An image capturing method with supplemental lighting modulation is applied to a monitoring apparatus having a lighting unit and an image detecting unit. The image capturing method includes dividing a working period of the lighting unit into at least one first sub-period and at least one second sub-period, driving the lighting unit to respectively output supplemental light with different intensity during the first sub-period and the second sub-period, driving the image detecting unit to respectively capture a set of monitoring images with a predetermined amount during the first sub-period and the second sub-period, comparing the monitoring image captured in the first sub-period with ones captured in the second sub-period, analyzing definition of the set of monitoring images, and selecting a corresponding monitoring image having the definition greater than a threshold to execute image recognition.

column12: Method for treating high concentration of hydrofluoric acid
column13: The present invention relates to a method for treating a high concentration of hydrofluoric acid, comprising steps of injecting a reaction carrier into a reaction chamber of a device for purification and treatment of hydrofluoric acid waste, jetting out of hydrofluoric acid waste as concurrently as adding Ca(OH)2 to the reaction chamber to be mixed with the reaction carrier for obtainment of a mixed solution containing a solid deposition of CaF2 and water, transferring the missed solution into a solid-liquid separation device to separate the solid deposition of CaF2 from the mixed solution, solely storing the solid deposition of CaF2 and allowing the water separated from the mixed solution to flow back to the reaction chamber serving as the reaction carrier again for recycling purposes. In this case, this invention has a simple technology and enables to be manipulated well, so as to effectively improve the efficiency of purifying a high concentration of hydrofluoric acid waste, increase resource recycling rates, avoid damages resulted from the high concentration of hydrofluoric acid waste to devices and operators, as well as further effectively avoid pipe clogging incurred by conventional methods for treating a high concentration of hydrofluoric acid waste. Besides, this invention also significantly promotes the efficiency and safety in treating and purifying the high concentration of hydrofluoric acid waste and considerably reduces treatment costs.
column14: KUNSHAN MINGKUAN ENVIRONMENTAL & ENERGY SAVING TECH CO LTD
column15: CHEN SHIH-CHUAN;;SONG RUO-SHAN

column12: METHOD OF ADJUSTING DISPLAY SIZE
column13: A method of adjusting a display size comprises the following steps: providing a display comprising a first substrate (100), a second substrate (200), and an image generation medium (300) disposed therebetween; providing a first cutting line on the first substrate (100), providing a second cutting line on the second substrate (200), wherein an orthographic projection of the first cutting line on the second substrate (200) does not overlap with the second cutting line; cutting, along the first cutting line, the first substrate (100) and the image generation medium (300) to form a first reserved portion (120) and a corresponding portion of the image generation medium (300); cutting, along the second cutting line, the second substrate (200) to form a second reserved portion (220) comprising a protruding portion (240) protruding outward in relation to the first reserved portion (120); applying an adhesive agent (430) on a surface of the protruding portion facing towards the first reserved portion (120) to enable the adhesive agent (430) to permeate between the first reserved portion (120) and the second reserved portion (220); and curing the adhesive agent (430). The embodiment can prevent the problem of inadequate sealing resulting from applying the adhesive agent to a location deviated too much, or forming gaps in the adhesive agent line.

column12: LIQUID CRYSTAL PANEL, DISPLAY AND TERMINAL
column13: Disclosed is a liquid crystal panel, comprising a first substrate, a second substrate and liquid crystal located between the first substrate and the second substrate, wherein the liquid crystal panel further comprises a first seal part to seal a gap between the first substrate and the second substrate, and the first seal is located along an edge of the first substrate, and the edge of the first substrate corresponding to the first seal part contracts inwardly relative to an edge of the second substrate close to the first seal part to expose a portion of the second substrate to form a protruding part, and the protruding part is employed to carry the first seal part. column12: LIQUID CRYSTAL PANEL, DISPLAY DEVICE AND TERMINAL
column13: Provided are a liquid crystal panel, a display device having a liquid crystal panel and a terminal. The liquid crystal panel comprises a first substrate (100), a second substrate (200), and a liquid crystal located between the first substrate (100) and the second substrate (200). The liquid crystal panel further comprises a first sealing portion (410) for sealing a gap between the first substrate (100) and the second substrate (200). The first sealing portion (410) is arranged along an edge of the first substrate (100). The edge of the first substrate (100) corresponding to the first sealing portion (410) is offset inwardly with respect to an edge of the second substrate (200) proximate to the first sealing portion (410), such that a portion of the second substrate (100) is exposed to form a protruding portion (220). The invention can prevent a liquid crystal panel from problems such as a discontinuous sealing portion and deviation of a spraying position, thereby avoiding poor sealing between a first substrate and a second substrate.

column12: Device and method for fixing objects on a multi-axis machine tool
column13: The device and method for fixing objects on a multi-axis machine tool of the present invention utilizes a set of orientation columns passing through a set of holes which is pre-set on a workpiece, and utilizes a set of bolts lock in the orientation columns for fixing the workpiece. Comparing to the prior art, the present invention utilizes the holes pre-set on the workpiece and the orientation columns to be precise match, makes the workpiece be fixed precisely in the same position no matter how much times the workpiece be fixed, further increases the repetitiveness of fixing and reduces the time of correcting, and moreover, prevents the deformation or inclination of the workpiece generated by clamping. Accordingly, the device and method for fixing objects on a multi-axis machine tool of the present invention is capable of playing more precision and fast advantages of multi-axis machine tool.

column12: ELECTRONIC DEVICE HAVING SECURITY STRUCTURE
column13: A electronic device includes a chassis, a panel, a cover and a security structure. The panel covers a side of the chassis. The cover covers another side of the chassis. The security structure includes a locking component, a positioning component and a linking shaft. The locking component is disposed on the panel and interfered with the chassis to lock the panel. The positioning component is disposed on the cover and interfered with the chassis to position the cover. The linking shaft is disposed between the locking component and the positioning component and stops the positioning component from being separated from the chassis. When a position of the locking component is adjusted to release the interference between the locking component and the chassis, the linking shaft is driven by the locking component to release the positioning component.
column15: LIN SHIH-LUNG;;CHEN TA-WEI;;CHEN YI-SHAN

column12: Catalyst composition for living free radical polymerization and process for polymerizing (meth) acrylic, vinyl, vinylidene, and diene monomers using the catalyst composition
column13:
A catalyst composition for living free radical polymerization. The catalyst composition includes a transition metal complex MX ₚ and a ligand, wherein M is a transition metal; X is halogen, NO ₂ , NCS, NCO, SCN, CN, N ₃ , SO ₄ , carboxylate group, or PF ₆ ; p is the valence of the transition metal, the ligand is represented by formula (I): 

    wherein R ¹ can be the same or different and is C ₁₋₂₀ alkyl, C ₆₋₂₀ aryl, C ₇₋₂₀ alkylaryl, C ₇₋₂₀ arylalkyl, or heterocyclic groups; R ² can be the same or different and is H, C ₁₋₂₀ alkyl, C ₆₋₂₀ aryl, C ₇₋₂₀ alkylaryl, C ₇₋₂₀ arylalkyl, heterocyclic groups, alkyl sulfide groups, nitrile groups, alkylsilyl, or ester groups; n is an integer of 0 to 6; and A is deleted or an S or O atom, wherein the molar ratio of the transition metal complex MX ₚ and the ligand is 1 to 4. The catalyst composition of the present invention can be used to polymerize (meth)acrylic, vinyl, vinylidene, and diene monomers, and the polymer obtained has narrow polydispersity.
column15: SHIH KUO-CHEN;;CHEN LI-JIUN;;CHAO YU-SHAN

column12: Catalyst composition for living free radical polymerization and process for polymerizing (meth)acrylic, vinyl, vinylidene, and diene monomers using the catalyst composition

column12: Switch module with secure mechanism and case having the switch module
column13: The present invention provides a case and a switch module with a secure mechanism. The case includes a housing having an accommodation portion; a cover, with a cover position, detachablely installed to the case to cover the accommodation portion; a switch module, with a secure mechanism installed to the case and located within an accommodation portion, including a pressing switch and a switch-changing element; and a switch-changing part, including a first pivot part pivoted to the case, a pressing part and a stop part, wherein the pressing part and the stop part jut from the first pivot part along different radial directions. The switch-changing part has a test position and a non-test position for rotating relative to the housing. When the switch-changing part is located at the test position, the pressing part is presses against the pressing switch to enable the pressing switch in an on-state, and the position of the stop part and the position of the cover position at least partly overlap so as to prevent the cover from installing at the case; and when the switch-changing part is located at the non-test position, the pressing part breaks away from the pressing switch, and the position of the stop part and the position of the cover position do not overlap so as to make the cover installed at the case. The present invention may avoid users of service to touch charged power supply by mistake.
column15: LIN SHIH-LUNG;;CHEN TA-WEI;;CHEN YI-SHAN

column12: Biomarker and method for prognosis of pancreatic duct adenocarcinoma
column13: Provided is a method for prognosis of a patient with pancreatic ductal adenocarcinoma (PDAC), including determining a methylation level of VAV1 gene in a genome sample from the patient. A hypermethylation of VAV1 gene body and a further hypomethylation of VAV1 promoter relative to the methylation level of VAV1 gene in a normal tissue indicates poor prognosis. Also provided is a biomarker for prognosis of PDAC, which is a VAV1 gene with aberrant methylation. Also provided is use of an inhibitor of methylation loss of VAV1 promoter or elevated methylation of VAV1 gene body for manufacture of pharmaceutical composition for treating PDAC.

column12: Method of forming IB-IIIA-VIA compounds
column13: Disclosed is a method of forming IB-IIIA-VIA compounds, which comprises the steps of: forming a reactive solution containing cations of Group IB and IIIA metal; adding a reducing agent into the reactive solution for allowing the cations of Group IB and IIIA metal to be reduced into metals; drying to obtain metallic powders; and performing a thermal treatment by using vapor of Group VIA elements or performing a thermal treatment with a Group VIA element so as to form IB-IIIA-VIA compounds. According to the invention, cations of Group IB and IIIA metal are reduced into metals by a reducing agent so as to form high active nano precursor powders, and subsequently, a thermal treatment of selenization, sulfidation or telluridation is performed by using a Group VIA element to form IB-IIIA-VIA compounds, which is applicable to the manufacture of photoelectric materials, thereby simplifying manufacturing processes and reducing the costs.

column12: Motor driving device and method thereof
column13: A motor driving device includes a first hysteresis comparator, a second hysteresis comparator, a logic circuit, a control unit, and an inverter circuit. The logic circuit receives a start signal or a start completion signal to output the first output signal as a commutation signal according to the start signal, or to output the second output signal as the commutation signal according to the start completion signal, clamps the second output signal by the first output signal, stops outputting the commutation signal after the potential state of the commutation signal is changed, and unclamps the second output signal with the first output signal and outputs the commutation signal in response to a difference voltage between the first input signal and the second input signal being greater than a positive value of the first hysteresis voltage or less than a negative value of the first hysteresis voltage.

column12: Motor driving device and method thereof
column13: A motor driving device includes a first hysteresis comparator, a second hysteresis comparator, a logic circuit, a control unit, and an inverter circuit. The logic circuit receives a start signal or a start completion signal, and outputs, according to the start signal, the first output signal of the first hysteresis comparator as a commutation signal, or uses, according to the start completion signal, the second output signal of the second hysteresis comparator as the commutation signal to be output, clamps the second output signal by the first output signal. After a potential state of the commutation signal is changed, the output of the commutation signal is stopped until a difference voltage between the first input signal and the second input signal is greater than a positive value of the first hysteresis voltage or smaller than a negative value of the first hysteresis voltage, the second output signal is unclamped by the first output signal, and the commutation signal is output.

column12: Composition of acidic hydrogen peroxide aqueous solution
column13: A composition of acidic hydrogen peroxide aqueous solution includes hydrogen peroxide, an acid-base regulator and an amino acid. The acid-base regulator includes an acid and an organic base. The amino acid has a structure represented by Formula (I). A pH value of the composition of acidic hydrogen peroxide aqueous solution is greater than or equal to 3.5 and is less than or equal to 4.6. Based on 100 parts by weight of the composition of acidic hydrogen peroxide aqueous solution, a content of the acid-base regulator is 10 parts by weight to 35 parts by weight, and a content of the amino acid is 0.08 parts by weight to its solubility. As such, it is favorable for enhancing the stability of the hydrogen peroxide. Also, it is favorable for removing metal ions with extraction method so as to conduct the liquid waste treatment or to reuse.

column12: METHOD AND SYSTEM FOR PROVIDING A USER INTERFACE FOR ACCESSING MULTIMEDIA ITEMS ON AN ELECTRONIC DEVICE
column13: A system and method for providing a user interface for accessing multimedia items using an electronic device determines a set of first level categories based on multimedia items associated with the electronic device. The system determines second level category graphics and first level category graphics corresponding to the set of first level categories. The first level category graphics are generated based on one or more of the second level category graphics associated with the first level category. The system then displays a first view that comprises some or all of the first level category graphics. In response to a user input selecting a particular first level category graphic, the system shows a second view that simultaneously displays first level category graphics and second level category graphics associated with the selected first level category. In response to a user input selecting a second level category, the system then displays information relating to a multimedia item associated with the selected second level category.

column12: Electronic apparatus and unlock method thereof
column13: An electronic apparatus is disclosed. The electronic apparatus includes a database, a distance sensor, a photography unit and a processing unit. The database stores at least one face data pre-entered by at least one authorized user. The distance sensor is used to sense a distance of a user relative to the electronic apparatus immediately. When the distance sensed by the distance sensor reduces, the photography unit captures a face image of the user. The processing unit is used to analyze the face image and compare the face image with the at least one face data. When the face image matches the at least one face data, the processing unit unlocks the electronic apparatus from a lock state.

column12: MANDREL FIN DESIGN FOR DOUBLE SEAL RING
column13: A semiconductor structure includes two circuit regions and two inner seal rings, each of which surrounds one of the circuit regions. Each inner seal ring has a substantially rectangular periphery with four interior corner stress relief (CSR) structures. The semiconductor structure further includes an outer seal ring surrounding the two inner seal rings. The outer seal ring has a substantially rectangular periphery without CSR structures at four interior corners of the outer seal ring. The outer seal ring includes a plurality of first fin structures located between each of the two inner seal rings and a respective short side of the outer seal ring. Each first fin structure is parallel with the respective short side of the outer seal ring. Lengths of the first fin structures gradually decrease along a direction from the inner seal rings to the respective short side of the outer seal ring.

column12: Method for measuring material trajectory in blast furnace
column13: A method for measuring a material trajectory in a blast furnace is described, which includes the following steps. A grid plane includes at least four grid nodes is formed by using light beams. An interior of the blast furnace is shot by a video camera to get an image of the grid plane. A plurality of nodes are defined on a mechanical drawing of the blast furnace corresponding to the grid nodes respectively. A relative parameter between coordinates of the nodes and coordinates of the corresponding grid nodes is calculated. Coordinates of outer edge bright points and coordinates of inner edge bright points of a material flow are obtained from the image. Coordinates of corresponding outer edge bright points and coordinates of corresponding inner edge bright points on the mechanical drawing of the coordinates of the outer edge bright points and the coordinates of the inner edge bright points are respectively calculated by using the relative parameter. Curve fitting treatments are respectively performed on the coordinates of the corresponding outer edge bright points and the coordinates of the corresponding inner edge bright points, to obtain an outer edge trajectory curve and an inner edge trajectory curve.

column12: Back light module
column13: The invention relates to a back light module applied to a display device. The back light module includes a light guide plate (LGP), a light source, a frame and a resistance component. The LGP includes a light receiving face. The light source faces the light receiving face. The light source and the LGP are positioned in the frame. The resistance component is disposed between the LGP and the frame and is near the light source. The resistance component includes a resistance surface and a incline trough. The resistance surface contacts the LGP. The incline trough has two inner wall surface. The inner wall surface is adjacent to the resistance surface and extends along a incline direction which is opposite the light receiving face and away from the resistance surface. Wherein the incline direction and a normal direction of the light receiving face are not perpendicular. Comparing to the prior art, the invention could ensure the optic quality of the back light module.

column12: FM STEREO TRANSMITTER AND DIGITIZED FREQUENCY MODULATION STEREO MULTIPLEXING CIRCUIT
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide an FM stereo transmitter using a digital multiplexer.

SOLUTION: A digital audio decoder decodes digital audio data, and obtains the audio signal of right and left channels. The audio signals of the right and left channels are input to an over-sampling unit circuit for sampling processing, and output to an FM stereo multiplexer. The FM stereo multiplexer processes the sampled audio signals of the right and left channels, and generates a main signal and a sub-signal. On the other hand, a switch signal and a pilot signal are obtained by an address counter so as to be output from a storage device. The main signal and the sub-signal and the pilot signal are compounded as digitized FM stereo data.

column12: FM stereo transmitter and a digitized frequency modulation stereo multiplexing circuit thereof
column13: A digitized FM (frequency modulation) stereo multiplexing circuit for an FM stereo transmitter has a digital audio I/O interface, a digitized FM stereo multiplexing circuit, a low-pass filter and an FM circuit. When a digital audio data is inputted, a digital audio decoder decodes the digital audio data to acquire left and right channel audio signals. The left and right channel audio signals are inputted to an over-sampling unit circuits to process sampling and then to output to an FM stereo multiplexer. The FM stereo multiplexer then generates a master signal and a secondary signal by processing the sampled left and right channel audio signals. In the meanwhile a switch signal and a pilot signal are acquired with an address counter to output from a memory unit. Then the master signal, the secondary signal and the pilot signal are combined as the digital FM stereo data.

column12: Method of multiple-subject image analysis using brain atlas
column13: Method of multiple-subject image analysis using brain atlas is disclosed. This method includes three steps. Firstly, provide a positron-emission tomography (PET) image, a magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) image and a brain atlas of a subject. Secondly, integrate the PET image, the MRI image and the brain atlas to generate a PET-MRI-brain atlas image. Finally, select automatically at least one region of interest (ROI) within the PET-MRI-brain atlas image and calculate the activated voxels in the ROI selected. The method mentioned can systematically integrate the results from different measuring systems as well as provide graphical user interface and related algorithm. Consequently, the drawbacks of each system can be compensated mutually.

column12: Method of block vector clipping and coding for screen content coding and video coding
column13: A method of video coding using coding modes including IntraBC mode (Intra-block copy mode) for a picture is disclosed. The system determines whether the current reference block is located above a current coding unit (CU) containing the current prediction unit (PU) in a vertical direction and whether the current reference block is located on a left side of the current CU in a horizontal direction based on the original block vector (BV). If both results are not true, the original BV is clipped to a clipped BV so that a relocated reference block corresponding to the clipped BV is above the current CU in the vertical direction or to the left side of the current CU in the horizontal direction. The clipped BV is used as a predictor for encoding or decoding of a current BV or used for IntraBC encoding or decoding of the current PU.

column12: Video coding method
column13: The invention provides a video coding method. A method of video coding using coding modes including Intra BC mode (Intra-block copy mode) for a picture is disclosed. The method determines whether thecurrent reference block is located above a current coding unit (CU) containing the current prediction unit (PU) in a vertical direction and whether the current reference block is located on a left side of the current CU in a horizontal direction based on the original block vector (BV). If both results are not true, the original BV is clipped to a clipped BV so that a relocated reference block corresponding to the clipped BV is above the current CU in the vertical direction or to the left side of the current CU in the horizontal direction. The clipped BV is used as a predictor for encoding or decoding of a current BV or used for Intra BC encoding or decoding of the current PU.
column15: CHUANG TZU-DER;;XU XIAOZHONG;;SUN YU-CHEN;;HSIANG SHIH-TA;;LIU SHAN

column12: Method for synthesis of C2-symmetric diamino diol mediated by titanium complexes
column13: A method for synthesis of C 2 -symmetric diamino diol mediated by titanium complexes is provided. A substituted-L-phenylalaninal undergoes pinacol coupling to yield the corresponding C 2 -symmetric (1S,2R,3R,4S)-1,4-diamino 2,3-diol in the presence of Cp 2 TiCl 2 /ZnCl 2 and zinc metal, mediated in good yield and highly selective. This titanium-catalyzed reaction yields diaminodiol, offering a convenient alternative method to the synthesis of C 2 -symmetric peptidic protease inhibitors. Consequently, the method allows to synthesize TL-3 via titanium complex in moderate yield.

column12: SELENIZATION PROCESS APPARATUS FOR GLASS SUBSTRATE
column13: A selenization process apparatus for a glass substrate includes a first heating unit disposed in a chamber; a conveying heating module disposed in the chamber and below the first heating unit to not only drive the glass substrate to move but also heat the glass substrate, wherein a thermal mark otherwise formed as a result of contact between the conveying heating module and the glass substrate is reduced with an inert gas; a selenium gas feeding module connected to the chamber to introduce selenium gas into the chamber; and a gas recycling module connected to the chamber to recycle the selenium gas and the inert gas. The glass substrate is prevented from staying at a soaking temperature above the softening point for a long period of time. Selenization temperature is increased to speed up the selenization process. The selenium gas and the inert gas are recycled and reused.

column12: Method of forming high dielectric constant dielectric layer by atomic layer deposition
column13: A method of forming a high dielectric constant (high-k) dielectric layer by atomic layer deposition includes the following steps. Cycles are performed one after another, and each of the cycles sequentially includes performing a first oxygen precursor pulse to supply an oxygen precursor to a substrate disposed in a reactor; performing a first oxygen precursor purge after the first oxygen precursor pulse; performing a chemical precursor pulse to supply a chemical precursor to the substrate after the first oxygen precursor purge; and performing a chemical precursor purge after the chemical precursor pulse. The first oxygen precursor pulse, the first oxygen precursor purge, the chemical precursor pulse, and the chemical precursor purge are repeated by at least 3 cycles. A second oxygen precursor pulse is performed to supply an oxygen precursor to the substrate after the cycles. A second oxygen precursor purge is performed after the second oxygen precursor pulse.

column12: Resident measurement system for charge level of blast furnace
column13: A resident measurement system for a charge level of a blast furnace includes a chamber, a servo system, a distance measurement unit, and a cooling-cleaning unit. The chamber is combined with a lateral furnace wall of the blast-furnace, covers an opening of the furnace wall, and has a pivoting hole. A pivot of the distance measurement unit is pivotally disposed at the pivoting hole, and the distance measurement unit is driven by the servo system to perform a motion with the pivot as a movement center, so as to measure the charge level. The cooling-cleaning unit is used to supply a high-pressure gas, which flows through the distance measurement unit to perform cooling and cleansing operations. The measurement system is small in dimension, and capable of scanning the charge level in an environment with high temperature, high concentration of dust, and high corrosion in the blast furnace furnace, establishing charge level information into a two-dimensional charge level mode, and obtaining a charge level profile distribution situation in real time, thereby promptly modifying a burden distribution mode.

column12: Pattern displaying device
column13: A pattern displaying device includes a light path changing element, a first light source, a second light source, and a control module. The light path changing element has first inclined surfaces to reflect light and arranged into a first predetermined pattern and second inclined surfaces to reflect light and arranged into a second predetermined pattern. The first light source is operable to emit light toward the first inclined surfaces to display the first predetermined pattern. The second light source is operable to emit light toward the second inclined surfaces in order to display the second predetermined pattern. The control module is electrically connected to the first and second light sources to control the first and second light source to emit light or not.

column12: Compound semiconductor device and compound semiconductor module
column13: A compound semiconductor device is provided, which includes an active structure, a semiconductor contact layer, an electrode, an insulating layer, a first opening, and a second opening. The active structure includes a first conductivity-type semiconductor layer, a second conductivity-type semiconductor layer, and an active layer located between the first conductivity-type semiconductor layer and the second conductivity-type semiconductor layer. The semiconductor contact layer is located on the second conductivity-type semiconductor layer and has a first opening. The electrode has an upper surface and completely covers the semiconductor contact layer and the first opening. The insulating layer covers the electrode and the active structure and has a second opening. The first conductivity-type semiconductor layer is exposed from the first opening. The electrode is exposed from the second opening. The first opening has a width which is larger than 90% of the width of the second opening.

column12: Online detection method for coking waste water sulfide content
column13: The invention relates to an online detection method for coking waste water sulfide content, which utilizes a platinum electrode to perform a potentiometric titration procedure. The detection method comprises first calculating and obtaining a ratio constant; supplying coking waste water into an online analytical device; then adding a titration solution to the coking waste water that is already inside the analytical device; using the platinum electrode to measure a titration end point potential; and finally computing the concentration of the sulfide base on the titration solution with known volume and concentration, the equivalent of sulfide under test, and the ratio constant. This detection method provided by this invention can be used online to directly detect the sulfide content in the coking waste water. As a result, this detection method is simple and fast.

column12: Device for selenizing glass substrate
column13: The present invention provides a device for selenizing a glass substrate, comprising a first heating unit disposed in a cavity body; a carrying and heating module disposed in the cavity body and below the first heating unit, and uses an inert gas to reduce thermal marks caused by contacting with a glass substrate, initiates the movement of and heats the glass substrate, and homogenizes the thermal distribution of the glass substrate by thermal convection of the inert gas; a selenium vapor inlet module which is connected to the cavity body to direct the selenium vapor into the cavity body; a gas recycling module which is connected to the cavity body is used to recycle the selenium vapor and the inert gas. In addition, the present invention is further provided with an upper heating module which applies the majority of energy on a film by appropriate wavelengths to rapidly increase or decrease the temperature of the film. Accordingly, the present invention protects the glass substrate from long exposure to a temperature higher than the softening point, achieves time saving by raising the temperature for selenization reaction according to requirements by the manufacturing process to reduce the time required for selenization reaction, and reduces material cost by reusing the selenium vapor and the inert gas in the recycled cavity body.

column12: RESIDENT MEASURING SYSTEM OF CHARGING LEVEL OF BLAST FURNACE
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a resident measuring system of a charging level of blast furnace.

SOLUTION: The resident measuring system of charging level of blast furnace includes a chamber, a servo system, a distance measuring unit, and a cooling-cleaning unit. The chamber is combined with a furnace side wall of a blast furnace, covers an opening in the furnace wall, and has a pivot hole. A pivot of the distance measuring unit is disposed to move axially in the pivot hole. The distance measuring unit is driven by the servo system and performs action together with the pivot as the center of the action, thereby measuring a charging level. Using the cooling-cleaning unit, high pressure gas is supplied, and the high-pressure gas flows through the distance measuring unit for cooling and cleaning work.

column12: Method for measuring filler of blast furnace, method for calculating compression ratio of filler, and method for calibrating microwave level instrument
column13: A method for measuring a filler of a blast furnace, a method for calculating a compression ratio of the filler, and a method for calibrating a microwave level instrument are described. In the method for measuring the filler of the blast furnace, many scanning steps are performed to an inner of the blast furnace by using a three-dimensional laser range finder to obtain various inner contour data groups. The inner contour data groups form a blast furnace contour. A furnace shape superposing step to superpose the blast furnace contour and a blast furnace original mechanical drawing onto a coordinate. A filling operation is performed to project various iron making materials into the blast furnace. A material surface of each iron making material is scanned by using the three-dimensional laser range finder to obtain a material surface data group of each iron making material.

column13: A smart medical box comprises a physiological measurement unit, a measuring terminal, a transmission unit, a power unit, a server, a storage unit, a comparison unit for, and an external input terminal. The measuring terminal is for a user, wherein the user has an identification part, and wherein the identification part has a sensor code. The measurement terminal comprises a sensing unit for the user to sense the identification piece to activate the physiological measurement unit to generate a physiological signal, and to measure a value as a detection signal. The transmission unit is for transmitting the detection signal. The power unit is for providing power to the sensing unit, the physiological measurement unit and the transmission unit. The server comprises a transmission module for receiving the detection signal. The storage unit is for storing the sensing code and the physiological signal. The comparison unit is for comparing whether the sensing code already exists in the storage unit. If yes, the storage unit stores the physiological signal corresponding to the sensing code. If not, the storage unit creates a new data comprising the sensor code and the physiological signal according to the sensor code, and registers the new data. The external input terminal is connected to the server terminal to register the new data.

column12: SCHEDULING DEVICE AND METHOD
column13: A scheduling device is provided, which includes a memory and a processor. The processor is configured to execute instructions to perform the following operations: (a) according to an order, are generating multiple candidate multi-production line schedules respectively, and each of the multiple candidate multi-production line schedules is used to assign multiple products of the order to multiple production lines; (b) performing a first crossover processing for each of the multiple candidate multi-production lines; (c) calculating respective first fitness scores of the multiple candidate multi-production line schedules for an elimination processing; (d) performing a second crossover processing for each of the multiple candidate multi-production lines; (e) calculating respective second fitness scores of the multiple candidate multi-production line schedules for an elimination processing; (f) determining whether an recursive end condition has been met according to the multiple second fitness scores.

column12: Peer-to-peer based secondary key search method and system for cluster database
column13: A peer-to-peer based secondary key search method and system for cluster databases is disclosed. A cluster database has a plurality of storage nodes and each storage node is assigned with a node number and stores a plurality of records. A search term input means couples to the plurality of storage nodes for retrieving a record at a storage node. The search term input means calculates a first node number based on a hash function of a secondary key, queries the first storage node with the secondary key for retrieving a corresponding primary key, calculates a second node number based on a hash function of the primary key, and then queries the second storage node with the primary key for retrieving a corresponding record.

column12: Lactobacillus plantarum strain, composition comprising the same, method of producing the same and its use for inhibiting or reducing oral pathogens

column12: Method for recycling the copper oxide from the sludge containing copper
column13: A method for recycling the copper oxide from the sludge containing copper is disclosed. The sludge containing copper is immersed in sulfuric acid so the liquid containing ionic iron and ionic copper is obtained. The jarosite method is introduced to separate the ionic iron from the ionic copper in the liquid, so the recyclable byproduct jarosite and the ionic copper liquid are formed. The ionic copper liquid can be refined to form highly purified expensive copper oxide by an oxidation process or ammonia immersion. Moreover, the wastewater of this recycling process can conform to the environmental standard. This process can recycle the wasted sludge to decrease the pollution and make the resource be repeatedly used.

column12: ELECTRONIC APPARATUS AND METHOD OF FABRICATING THE SAME
column13: A method of fabricating an electronic apparatus having an active region and a peripheral region surrounding the active region is described. A first main device and a second main device are provided. An optical clear liquid adhesive (OCLA) is applied between the first main device and the second main device and within the active region. A photo-mask having a transparent region and an opaque region is provided above the second main device, and the transparent region corresponds to the peripheral region. An OCLA diffusion process is performed such that the OCLA diffuses from the active region to the peripheral region. During the OCLA diffusion process, a first irradiating process with the photo-mask is performed, such that the OCLA diffusing to the peripheral region is partially cured. After removing the photo-mask, a second irradiating process is performed, such that the OCLA is completely cured.

column12: Failure detection apparatus and failure detection method
column13: A failure detection apparatus and a failure detection method are provided. In the method, the to-be-determined value of electrical and mechanical equipment is received. The to-be-determined value is related to the operation status of the electrical and mechanical equipment. The parameter value is determined according to the to-be-determined value. The parameter value is used to be inputted into a neural network. The failure type corresponding to the parameter value is determined through an identifying model. The relation between the failure type and the parameter value is trained for the identifying model through the neural network. Accordingly, the accuracy of failure identification and the identifying efficiency could be improved.

column12: Low-temperature catalytic incineration of cooking-oil fume using hydrophobic noble-metal catalyst supported on honeycomb
column13: The present invention provides a high-efficient method and equipment to remove cooking-oil fume and destroy the odor molecules. The present invention develops hydrophobic carbon catalyst, which is prepared by loading noble-metal on a hydrophobic support for low-temperature combustion with high activity. The hydrophobic noble-metal catalyst can completely oxidize volatile organic compounds (VOCs) at low temperature, so that less fuel is required to sustain the working temperature. In addition, the activity of the hydrophobic noble-metal catalyst can be enhanced because the moisture of the kitchen fume has negligible effect on the hydrophobic surface. Thus the odor of fume can be completely removed. The present invention provides a catalytic honeycomb system that allows low-pressure drop in the duct of the kitchen hood. The present invention provides a total solution to removal oil fume from kitchens so the hazardous problem can be reduced for the urban population.

column13: The present invention relates to a vapor deposition equipment for fabricating CIGS film, in which a Se vapor deposition module, a In/Ga/In linear vapor deposition module and a Cu linear vapor deposition module are integrated in an identical vacuum chamber, used for fabricating the CIGS absorber layers on a flexible solar cell substrate by an automatic manufacturing process in accordance with an unwinding module, a heating device, a heat reducing device, a speed-controlling roller module, a cooling module, and a winding module. column12: Compound liquid for regulating blood lipids capable of reducing the triglyceride content in the liver while regulating the cholesterol content in the blood
column13: The present invention provides a compound liquid for regulating blood lipids, including lactic acid bacteria culture solution and a cooked red quinoa (Chenopodium formosanum Koidz) powder, wherein the lactic acid bacteria culture solution is obtained by culturing Lactobacillus plantarum (BCRC No. 10069) in a medium containing a deep seawater concentrate; and the cooked red quinoa powder is prepared by steaming, freeze-drying and grinding red quinoa. Preferably, if the total weight of the lactic acid bacteria culture solution is 100 parts by weight, the cooked red quinoa powder is 22-37 parts by weight. The deep seawater concentrate is obtained by distilling to desalinate and nanofiltrating seawater of 200 meter or more below sea level. The compound liquid of the present invention can reduce the triglyceride content in the liver while regulating the cholesterol content in the blood.

column12: Method and system for automatically interpreting cardiac function through deep learning models
column13: The present invention discloses a method and a system for automatically interpreting cardiac function through deep learning models. In the method, an area of a heart to be marked can be calculated, and an outer contour of the heart can be obtained. The outer contour is divided into multiple segments. A maximum area is calculated from a diastolic heart, and a minimum area is calculated from a systolic heart from the continuous cardiac images. Accordingly, a union-set image and an intersection-set image of the maximum area and the minimum area can be obtained. Afterwards, the union-set image is used to subtract the intersection-set image, and the subtraction is referred to for automatically interpreting abnormal contractions in multiple areas of the heart while introducing an abnormal interpreting model.

column12: Prediction method and prediction system for an abnormal heart function by deep learning models
column13: The present invention discloses a prediction method for an abnormality of the heart function by deep learning models. The prediction method comprises: providing medical images, the medical images consists of multiple frames of heart domain and non-heart domain images; the heart domain and non-heart domain images produces aberration by contrast agent; extracting one of the medical images as target frame; judging the aberration of the target frame, for entirely marking outer contour of heart domain on the target frame; calculating the dimensions of the outer contour, for determining the maximum dimensions of the maximum diastolic status and the minimum dimensions of the minimum systolic status of the heart domain; calculating and transforming the maximum dimensions and the minimum dimensions for obtaining ejection fraction; outputting the ejection fraction for determining whether the heart domain is abnormal or normal, in order to judge the heart domain automatically.

column13: The present invention relates to a complex probiotic composition for alleviating overactive bladder syndrome and use thereof. column12: Multilayer antioxidant coating lactic acid bacteria (MAOC-LAB) microencapsule and method of producing the same
column13: The present invention relates to a multilayer antioxidant coating lactic acid bacteria (MAOC-LAB) microencapsule and a method of producing the same. The MAOC-LAB microencapsule has a multi-layered concentric stereostructure, which is formed by inserting polar molecules of short chains onto a probiotic cell wall of a microbial core, followed by coating two layers of a saccharide molecule layer and a bipolar emulsion protein layer of antioxidation, respectively. The resultant MAOC-LAB microencapsule can beneficially improve the characteristics of the probiotics, such as moisture- and deliquescent- resistance, storage stability, oxidation resistance, gastric acid resistance and enzymatic digestion resistance.

column12: Method and apparatus for coding video data
column13: The invention provides a method and apparatus for coding video data. The video data is configured into a Base Layer (BL) and an Enhancement Layer (EL), and the EL has higher spatial resolution or better video quality than the BL. The method comprises following steps: receiving information corresponding to input data related with EL from media or a processor; identifying motion data related with aplurality of sub-blocks of BL; using the prediction information containing the motion data related with a plurality of sub-blocks of BL, coding input data related with EL; and using representative motion data of multiple sub-blocks in a compression area to compress motion data related with a plurality of sub-blocks of BL; wherein the motion data is compressed after input data related with EL is decoded, and the compressed motion data is stored in other video frames. By using the method and apparatus, higher performance and more flexibility are obtained.

column12: Method and apparatus of scalable video coding
column13: A method and apparatus for coding video data by using Inter prediction mode or Merge mode in a video coding system are disclosed. The video data is configured into a Base Layer (BL) and an Enhancement Layer (EL), and the EL has higher spatial resolution or better video quality than the BL. In one embodiment, at least one information piece of motion information associated with one or more BL blocks in the BL is identified. A motion vector prediction (MVP) candidate list or a Merge candidate list for the selected block in the EL is then determined, where the at least one information piece associated with the one or more BL blocks in the BL is included in the MVP candidate list or the Merge candidate list. The input data associated with the selected block is coded or decoded by using the MVP candidate list or the Merge candidate list.

column12: External composition for wound healing containing Lactobaccilus fermentation product and use thereof
column13: The present invention relates to an external composition for wound healing containing Lactobaccilus fermentation product and a use thereof. The Lactobaccilus fermentation product serves as an effective component, which is a bacteria-free concentrated filtrate fermented by Lactobacillus plantarum and loaded onto an absorbent carrier or a carrying agent. column12: Use of lactic acid bacteria for increasing resistance against enterovirus 71
column13: The present invention relates to a use of lactic acid bacteria for preparing composition of increasing resistance against enterovirus 71 (EV71), in which the lactic acid bacteria are selected from the group consisting of Lactobacillus. plantarum GKM3, GK4, GKD7, GKK1, L. paracasei GKS6, L. fermentum GKF3, L. casei GKC1, Bifidobacterium. lactis GKK2, L. reuteri GKR1, L. rhamnosus GKLC1, GKY7, Pediococcus. acidilactici GKA4, P. pentosaceus GKP4, B. longum GKL7, B. bifidum GKB2, B. breve GKV1, L. brevis GKJOY, GKL9, B. animals GKBA and any combination thereof. The composition includes a dead bacterial culture of lactic acid bacteria as an active ingredient, thereby reducing a probability of the EV71 infecting animal cells in vitro, as well as reducing a cytotoxicity of the EV71 in vitro.

column13: The present invention relates to a use of lactic acid bacteria for preparing composition of increasing resistance against enterovirus 71 (EV71), in which the lactic acid bacteria are selected from the group consisting of Lactobacillus plantarum GKM3, GK4, GKD7, GKK1, L. paracasei GKS6, L. fermentum GKF3, L. casei GKC1, Bifidobacterium lactis GKK2, L. reuteri GKR1, L. rhamnosus GKLC1, GKY7, Pediococcus acidilactici GKA4, P. pentosaceus GKP4, B. longum GKL7, B. bifidum GKB2, B. breve GKV1, L. brevis GKJOY, GKL9, B. animals GKBA and any combination thereof. The composition includes a dead bacterial culture of lactic acid bacteria as an active ingredient, thereby reducing a probability of the EV71 infecting animal cells in vitro, as well as reducing a cytotoxicity of the EV71 in vitro.

column12: Method of manufacturing Al and Al alloy sputtering target
column13: A method of manufacture sputtering target is disclosed. This method uses direct-chill casting technique to manufacture various kinds of Al and Al alloy ingots. The Al alloy ingots cast can be cut directly into the desired sputtering target of Al and Al alloy without the follow up forging process. This method provides advantages of less engineering process required, higher production, and higher yield of qualified products. Furthermore, the sputtering target product has the advantage of less grain size, tiny educt material, and uniformity composition.

column12: Method of manufacturing aluminum and aluminum alloy sputtering targets
column13: A manufacturing method of sputtering targets uses a direct-chill method to fabricate various aluminum and aluminum alloy ingots. Without the need of follow-up forging processes, the fabricated aluminum alloy ingots can be cut to attain aluminum and aluminum alloy sputtering targets. In addition, the fabricated targets have small grains, fine precipitate phases, and homogeneous composition.

column12: Slurry recycling method and slurry recycling apparatus for the same
column13: A slurry recycling method used for an operating slicing apparatus, which has an used slurry after slicing, includes the steps as follows. Transferring the used slurry to a first centrifuge, the used slurry is separated into a first light-liquid and a first heavy-liquid by the first centrifuge. Transferring the first light-liquid to a cyclone module, the first light-liquid is separated into an over flow and an underflow by the cyclone module. Transferring the over flow to a second centrifuge, the over flow is separated into a second light-liquid and a second heavy-liquid by the second centrifuge. The first heavy-liquid, the underflow, and the second light-liquid are suitably provided to the operating slicing apparatus, and the second heavy-liquid is an abandon. Besides, the instant disclosure also provides a slurry recycling apparatus for the above slurry recycling method.

column12: Vacuum process system and intelligent valve thereof
column13: A vacuum process system and an intelligent valve thereof are disclosed. The vacuum process system comprises the intelligent valve, a peripheral unit and a process chamber, where the peripheral unit and the intelligent valve provide a corresponding operating environment and a movement mode based on operating parameters. The intelligent valve inputs sensing data into a learning training model for edge computing and decision making to update the operating parameters of the peripheral unit and the intelligent valve online correspondingly so that the process chamber can perform the vacuum process.

column12: Reinforced frame automatic inspection system, computer readable storage device and operation method thereof
column13: The present invention relates to an automatic inspection system of a reinforced frame and operation method thereof. It mainly obtains a depth image of a reinforced frame and a three-dimensional coordinate information corresponding to the depth image, and automatically generates a segmentation results corresponding to the depth image with a image segmentation model, and after obtaining the at least one value of the reinforcement inspection item of the reinforced frame according to the three-dimensional coordinate information corresponding to the segmentation results, displaying an inspection result including the at least one value of the reinforcement inspection item. In the application, by automatically recognizing and generating the segmentation results to quickly obtain the at least one value of the reinforcement inspection item, the purpose of improving the convenience of inspecting the reinforced frame is achieved.

column12: FACILITY USED FOR STEPS OF SELENIZATION AND SULFURIZATION OF GLASS SUBSTRATE
column13: PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a facility used for steps of selenization and sulfurization of a glass substrate.SOLUTION: The present invention relates to a facility used for steps of selenization and sulfurization of a glass substrate, and particularly relates to a facility of low cost and no toxicity, which can be used for steps of selenization and sulfurization of a large-area glass substrate under a normal atmospheric pressure environment. The facility used for steps of selenization and sulfurization of a glass substrate according to the invention can thermally decompose selenium or sulfur into highly activated small molecules by a high temperature. Also, the facility allows highly activated selenium or sulfur molecules to be obtained by means of plasma, especially linear atmospheric pressure plasma, and it enables the achievement of large-area, uniform selenization and sulfurization on a single glass substrate by uniformly distributing the selenium or sulfur molecules, and reciprocating the glass substrate precisely.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 11

column12: Integration type rapid selenization and sulfurization process equipment for providing a process with large area, low cost, nontoxicity and applicability to normal or vacuum pressure environment
column13: The integration type rapid selenization and sulfurization process equipment of the present invention makes use of three chambers to perform rapid thermal processing, selenization and sulfurization on a glass substrate, respectively, so as to prevent the glass substrate from being kept at a holding temperature above the softening point for a long time and increase the selenization/sulfurization temperature of a thin film according to a process requirement thereby reducing the time required for holding the selenization/sulfurization temperature to achieve the energy-saving and time-saving effect. By enabling the glass substrate to reciprocate in the chambers, the overall temperature of the glass substrate becomes more uniform. Moreover, the recycled liquid selenium/sulfur and inert gas can be reused, thereby reducing the material cost.

column13: Un compuesto de Fórmula (I): **Fórmula** en la que es un enlace sencillo o un enlace doble; n es 0, 1, o 2; R1 es SO2Ra, en la que Ra es arilo o heteroarilo; en la que el arilo se selecciona de un sistema de anillo aromático monocíclico de 6 carbonos, bicíclico de 10 carbonos o tricíclico de 14 carbonos monovalente; y en la que el heteroarilo se selecciona de un sistema de anillo aromático monovalente monocíclico de 5-8 elementos, bicíclico de 8-12 elementos o tricíclico de 11-14 elementos, que tiene uno o más heteroátomos, en donde el uno o más heteroátomos se seleccionan independientemente de O, N, S y Se; en la que el arilo o el heteroarilo pueden estar opcionalmente sustituidos con sustituyentes seleccionados de alquilo C1-C10, alquenilo C2-C10, alquinilo C2-C10, cicloalquilo C3-C20, cicloalquenilo C3-C20, heterocicloalquilo C1-C20, heterocicloalquenilo C1-C20, alcoxi C1-C10, arilo, ariloxi, heteroarilo, heteroariloxi, amino, alquilamino C1-C10, arilamino, hidroxi, halo, oxo (O=), tioxo (S=), tio, sililo, alquiltio C1-C10, ariltio, alquilsulfonilo C1-C10, arilsulfonilo, acilamino, aminoacilo, aminotioacilo, amidino, mercapto, amido, tioureido, tiocianato, sulfonamido, guanidina, ureido, ciano, nitro, acilo, tioacilo, aciloxi, carbamido, carbamilo (-C(O)NH2), carboxilo (-COOH) y éster carboxílico, en donde el arilo y el heteroarilo también pueden estar condensados entre sí; y R2 es H, alquilo, NHC(O)-CH=CH-C(O)NRcRd o C(O)NRcRd, en donde cada uno de Rc y Rd, independientemente, es H o hidroxi; cada uno de R3, R4, R5 y R6, independientemente, es H, alquilo, CH=CH-C(O)NRcRd, NHC(O)-CH=CH- C(O)NRcRd o C(O)NRcRd, en la que uno de Rc y Rd es H y el otro es hidroxi; siempre que uno o más de R2, R3, R4, R5 y R6 tenga las siguientes definiciones: R2 es NHC(O)-CH=CH- C(O)NRcRd; o R3, R5 y R6 es, independientemente, CH=CH-C(O)NRcRd o NHC(O)-CH=CH-C(O)NRcRd, o R4 es C(O)NHOH, CH=CH-C(O)NRcRd o NHC(O)-CH=CH-C(O)NRcRd.

column12: Selenium vulcanization processing equipment of one-glass substrate rapid heating and selenization/vulcanization respectively for the glass substrate through two cavity bodies
column13: The application discloses a selenium vulcanization processing equipment of one-glass substrate. By rapid heating and selenization/vulcanization respectively for the glass substrate through two cavity bodies, it can avoid the glass substrate being at a holding temperature over a softening point for a long time. Film selenization/vulcanization temperature can be improved in accordance with requirements of fabrication to reduce selenization/vulcanization time for holding temperature, thereby achieving power-saving and time-saving effect; temperatures of all portions of the glass substrate can be more uniform by causing the glass substrate to move back and forth in the chambers; selenization/vulcanization gas can be distributed more uniformly on the glass substrate during selenization/vulcanization operation; furthermore, recovered liquid-state selenium/ sulfur and inert gas can be re-used for reducing material cost.

column12: Electronic device and method for accelerating generation of simulation result of simulation software
column13: An electronic device and a method for accelerating a generation of a simulation result of a simulation software are provided. The method includes: obtaining input data; generating fake data according to the input data; inputting a first fake feature of the fake data to the simulation software to generate a first fake simulation result; obtaining a user-defined feature; calculating a first similarity between the first fake feature and the user-defined feature; generating, based on the first similarity, an approximate simulation result matching with the user-defined feature according to the first fake simulation result; and outputting the approximate simulation result.

column12: ULTRASONIC SENSOR DEVICES, COMPONENT MODULE THEREOF AND METHOD FOR MAKING THE ULTRASONIC SENSOR DEVICE
column13: An ultrasonic sensor device includes a sensing unit and a component module disposed in a casing. The sensing unit is configured to generate a sensing signal in response to receipt of an external sound wave. The component module includes a base seat, a circuit unit and a cushioning unit. The base seat has a base board and a lower seat portion under the base board. The base board is formed with a recess. The circuit unit is disposed in the recess, is coupled electrically to the sensing unit for receiving the sensing signal therefrom, and is to be coupled electrically to an external electronic circuit. The cushioning unit is disposed at the base seat, and is proximate to the sensing unit.

column12: SELENIZATION/SULFURIZATION PROCESS APPARATUS FOR USE WITH SINGLE-PIECE GLASS SUBSTRATE
column13: A selenization/sulfurization process apparatus for use with a single-piece glass substrate is characterized by two chambers for heating up a glass substrate quickly and performing selenization/sulfurization on the glass substrate to not only prevent the glass substrate from staying at a soaking temperature of a softening point for a long period of time but also increase the thin-film selenization/sulfurization temperature according to the needs of the process to thereby reduce the duration of soaking selenization/sulfurization, save energy, and save time. The glass substrate undergoes reciprocating motion in the chambers to not only attain uniform temperature throughout the glass substrate but also distribute a selenization/sulfurization gas across the glass substrate uniformly during the selenization/sulfurization operation. The recycled liquid selenium/sulfur and inert gas are reusable to thereby reduce material costs.

column12: APPARATUS FOR PERFORMING SELENIZATION AND SULFURIZATION PROCESS ON GLASS SUBSTRATE
column13: An apparatus for performing a selenization and sulfurization process on a glass substrate is introduced. A low-cost, non-toxic selenization and sulfurization process is performed on a large-area glass substrate in a normal-pressure environment with the apparatus to turn element selenium or sulfur into small molecules of high activity at high temperature by pyrolysis or by plasma, especially linear atmospheric pressure plasma. The process is finalized by dispersing the selenium or sulfur molecules uniformly and allowing the glass substrate to undergo reciprocating motion precisely, thereby achieving large-area, uniform selenization and sulfurization of the one-piece glass substrate.

column12: MUSCLE AMOUNT MEASUREMENT METHOD
column13: To provide a muscle amount measurement method.SOLUTION: A muscle amount measurement method includes: a first selection step for frame-selecting a fascia area by a computer tomographic photographing scan image to acquire frame selection information so as to include muscles within a fascia area selection range under a condition that the computer tomographic photographing scan image is provided, a window width is within a range from 300 HU to 500 HU, and also a window level is within a range from 40 HU to 50 HU; and a second selection step for calculating a pixel value within the fascia area frame-selected to acquire muscle information under a condition that an HU value of the computer tomographic photographing scan image is within a range from 29 HU to 150 HU.SELECTED DRAWING: Figure 1

column12: Collar removing clamp for HDP chamber
column13: A clamp for quickly, effectively and safely removing a cathode collar from an HDP deposition chamber for routine maintenance, cleaning or replacement of the collar. The clamp includes a pair of clamp plates which are capable of pivoting movement on respective ends of a connecting rod. A clamp shoe for gripping a corresponding edge of the annular collar is provided on the bottom end of each clamp plate, and a turnbuckle is fitted with a pair of threaded shafts which engage the upper end portions of the respective clamp plates. By rotating the turnbuckle, the threaded shafts are advanced away from each other against the clamp plates, which pivot on the connecting rod and cause the clamp shoes to tightly engage respective edges of the collar. The clamp is grasped to lift the collar from the chamber and replace the collar in the chamber after cleaning or maintenance.

column12: MULTI-LAYER HIGH-K GATE DIELECTRIC STRUCTURE
column13: A transistor includes a gate structure that has a first gate dielectric layer and a second gate dielectric layer. The first gate dielectric layer is disposed over the substrate. The first gate dielectric layer contains a first type of dielectric material that has a first dielectric constant. The second gate dielectric layer is disposed over the first gate dielectric layer. The second gate dielectric layer contains a second type of dielectric material that has a second dielectric constant. The second dielectric constant is greater than the first dielectric constant. The first dielectric constant and the second dielectric constant are each greater than a dielectric constant of silicon oxide.

column12: MEHRSCHICHTIGE HIGH-K-GATEDIELEKTRIKUMSTRUKTUR
column13: Ein Transistor enthält eine Gatestruktur, die eine erste Gatedielektrikumschicht und eine zweite Gatedielektrikumschicht aufweist. Die erste Gatedielektrikumschicht ist über dem Substrat angeordnet. Die erste Gatedielektrikumschicht enthält eine erste Art von dielektrischem Material, das eine erste Dielektrizitätskonstante hat. Die zweite Gatedielektrikumschicht ist über der ersten Gatedielektrikumschicht angeordnet. Die zweite Gatedielektrikumschicht enthält eine zweite Art von dielektrischem Material, das eine zweite Dielektrizitätskonstante hat. Die zweite Dielektrizitätskonstante ist größer als die erste Dielektrizitätskonstante. Die erste Dielektrizitätskonstante und die zweite Dielektrizitätskonstante sind jeweils größer als eine Dielektrizitätskonstante von Siliziumoxid.

column12: METHOD FOR MEASURING MUSCLE MASS
column13: The present invention relates to a method for measuring muscle mass, including: a first selection step, wherein a frame selection information is obtained by using a frame to select a fascia region from a provided computed tomography image under the condition that the window width ranges from 300 HU to 500 HU and the window level ranges from 40 HU to 50 HU, wherein the selected range of the fascia region includes a muscle; and a second selection step, wherein a muscle information of the muscle is obtained by calculating a pixel value in the frame-selected fascia region under the condition that the HU value of the CT image ranges from -29 HU to 150 HU.

column12: Method for measuring muscle mass
column13: The present invention relates to a method for measuring muscle mass including: a first selection step, at which a computed tomography image is provided, and under the condition that the window width ranges from 300 HU to 500 HU and the window level ranges from 40 HU to 50 HU, a fascia region on the CT image is selected by a frame to obtain a frame selection information, wherein the selected region of the fascia region includes a muscle; and a second selection step, under the condition that the HU value of the CT image ranges from -29 HU to 150 HU, an image value in the frame-selected fascia region is calculated so as to obtain a muscle information of the muscle.

column12: Air sterilization device with low aerosol bounce
column13: An air sterilization device with low aerosol bounce includes an air conditioning pipe, a porous filter media, and a UV light generator. This porous filter media, it is secured on the fixing portion. This porous filter media has many irregularly distributed channels. The channel is coated with a coating layer having a thickness between 10 μm to 1000 μm sticking aerosols for avoiding bounce effect. The UV light generator can emit UV light to kill biological aerosols. It is suitable for long-term usage. So, the bounce effect of aerosols can be significantly reduced. The maintenance cost is low. The sterilization effect is excellent. Plus, the flow rate of the air conditioning system remains high.

column13: A multi-stage horizontal elutriator includes a flow inlet, a flow outlet, a hollow container that is disposed between said flow inlet and said flow outlet. column12: ELECTRON MICROSCOPE
column13: An electron microscope includes a charged particle beam generator, a detector, a film and a bearing unit. The charged particle beam generator generates a first charged particle beam to bomb an object. The detector detects a second charged particle from the object to form an image. The film disposes on downstream of charged particle beam generator and has a first surface and a second surface. A space between charged particle beam generator and the first surface of film is a vacuum environment. The bearing unit disposes at a side of second surface of film and has a bearing surface and a back surface. The object disposes on the bearing surface of the bearing unit and a distance between an analyzed surface of the object and the film is less than a predetermined spacing. A liquid space exists between the analyzed surface and the film to be filled a liquid.

column12: Method of forming a display panel
column13: A method of forming a display panel includes providing a first substrate, and coating the first substrate with an alignment material. Next, after a pre-baking process is performed on the alignment material and before a seal is dispensed, an UV treatment or a plasma treatment is carried out on the alignment material to passivate the monomer impurities mixed in the alignment material. Afterward, a second substrate is provided, the seal is dispensed on the first or the second substrate, and next a liquid crystal layer is formed between the first and the second substrates. Thus, the mura effect coursed by the monomer impurities is effectively decreased.

column12: DEHUMIDIFYING APPARATUS
column13:
PROBLEM TO BE SOLVED: To provide a dehumidifying apparatus formed by combining a charged particle regeneration and desorption with adsorbing type drying.

SOLUTION: A continuous charged circulation air flow is generated, moisture on an adsorption part is desorbed to replace a humidifying apparatus of a known electric heat desorption type. Use of a charged particle desorbing/drying technology and driving force and an electric field formed by the high energy charged particles allows direct alteration of adsorption force between water molecules and the dehumidifying structure, to desorb humidity on the absorption part. Moisture desorption effect can be obtained with reduced electric power, replacing the known electric heating system of high electric power consumption, to remarkably save energy.

column12: Dehumidifier and a regenerator thereof
column13: The present invention provides a desiccant type dehumidifier, which is capable of absorbing the moisture through a desiccant and generating a continuous charged regenerating flow for desorbing water vapor from the desiccant. It replaces the conventional themal-desorption-type dehumidifier which regenerated by electric heater. The present invention utilizes charged medium to form an electric field and driving force for reducing the adsorptive force between the water molecular and the desiccant and then desorbing the water from the desiccant. Since the present invention consumes low power to generate charged medium for removing water from the desiccant, it is capable of reducing the energy cost during dehumidification and replacing conventional desorption system made by electric heater having high energy cost.

column12: Lactobacillus plantarum and application thereof in reducing uric acid, improving allergy and reducing blood sugar
column13: The invention provides lactobacillus plantarum and a method for reducing uric acid by using the same. The invention relates to a lactobacillus plantarum GKM3 with a specific gene sequence, in particular to a lactobacillus plantarum GKM3 with a specific gene sequence, which has acid resistance, alkali resistance and/or cell adsorption capacity and can achieve the effects of eliminating body fat, reducing blood fat, reducing hepatomegaly, reducing liver function indexes, resisting inflammation, reducing uric acid and improving allergy and/or reducing blood sugar. column12: Novellactobacillus paracasei GKS6 for improving metabolic syndromes, its medium, incubation method, use, pharmaceutical composition and edible composition
column13: The present invention discloses a novel Lactobacillus paracasei GKS6 (with an accesstion No. BCRC 910788 for a biological material deposit) for improving metaboilic syndrome. The present invention further discloses the GKS6 strain's medium, its incubation method, use, pharmaceutical composition and edible composition. The GKS6 strain can tolerate against the acidity in the stomach and the bile salt in the gastrointestinal tract, can effectively decrease body weight, hypertrophy in organs, the level of lipid in the liver, blood lipid, hepatomegaly and liver function indexs, reduce the levels of the visceral and the subcutaneous adipose tissues, and remove body fat. The GKS6 strain can be used in preventing and/or treating metabolic relevant diseases, reducing the obesity induced by high fat diet, and increasing the dischargement of body fat to reduce the obesity induced by the high fat diet.

column12: Display device and manufacturing method thereof
column13: A display device is arranged adjacent to the decoration layer and includes a display panel. The display panel includes a first substrate, a second substrate, active elements, a display medium layer, and a first polarizer. The first substrate is closer to the outer surface of the display device than the second substrate. The first polarizer is located at the first substrate and includes a reflective layer including a first wire grid portion and a color adjustment layer including a second wire grid portion. The color adjustment layer is closer to the outer surface of the display device than the reflective layer. The color adjustment layer is configured to absorb light of part of wavelength, so that the first polarizer of the display device in a closed state and the decoration layer belong to a same color family.

column12: SPINAL DYNAMIC STABILIZATION DEVICE
column13: A spinal dynamic stabilization device for maintaining an anatomical height between two adjacent vertebras is provided. Each vertebra includes a spinous process and two symmetric pedicles. The spinal dynamic stabilization device includes a supporting member, at least one anchoring member, and at least one connecting member. The supporting member is disposed between the spinous processes. The anchoring member is fixed in one of the vertebra via one of the pedicles. The connecting member connects the supporting member to the anchoring member, fixing a relative position between the supporting member and the anchoring member, further fixing a relative position between the vertebras.

column12: Optical image physiological monitoring system with radar detection assistance
column13: The present invention relates to an optical image physiological monitoring system with radar detection assistance. The system analyzes the characteristic part of the thoracic cavity in an optical image and determines a position of the thoracic cavity after the optical image is received. The system controls an radar detector to aim the thoracic cavity and then receives the optical images and measured distance values to follow the position of the thoracic cavity. The system analyzes the change of the measured distance values obtained during the positions of the characteristic part of the thoracic cavity remains within a position change range. Therefore, the respiratory rate of the body is determined according to the analyzing result.
